messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /api/upload

- all methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false

- POST: true

- OPTIONS: false

- TRACE: false

- GET: false

- PUT: false

- DELETE: false

- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- In server.js the router from routes/uploadRoutes.js is mounted with app.use('/api/upload', uploadRoutes); so the router's '/' becomes the full path '/api/upload'.
- In routes/uploadRoutes.js the router explicitly defines only router.post('/', ...). No other HTTP methods (router.get, router.put, router.delete, router.patch, router.options, router.head, router.trace or app.all) are implemented, so only POST is accepted according to the code.
- The "all methods acceptable" flag is false because there is no app.all or equivalent that would accept all methods.
- HEAD is not implemented separately; Express only supplies automatic HEAD responses for GET routes, but no GET route exists here, so HEAD is not handled by the code.
- OPTIONS, TRACE and the other methods are not defined anywhere in the provided code, so they are marked false.
